2. INFORMATION WE COLLECT
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

We collect the following categories of information.

2.1 Information you provide
  - Account and profile data: name, phone number, email address, password
    (stored in hashed form), profile photo, role (shipper, carrier, or
    dispatcher), and company/organization details.
  - Business content: loads and transport posts you create, shipment and
    order details, pickup and delivery addresses, cargo descriptions,
    pricing, vehicle and driver assignments, and ratings/reviews you submit.
  - Documents and images: proof-of-delivery (POD) photos, transport/vehicle
    photos, and other documents or files you upload through the App.
  - Communications: messages, attachments, and shared locations you send
    through the in-app chat, and any correspondence you have with our support
    team.

2.2 Location information
  - Foreground location: when you grant permission, we use your device's
    location to center maps, set delivery search areas, and pre-fill pickup
    or delivery points.
  - Background ("Always") location: if you are a driver/carrier on an
    assigned delivery, and you grant the "Always" location permission, the App
    shares your location while you drive — including when the App is in the
    background or closed — so that shippers and dispatchers can track the
    delivery's progress. Background tracking begins when a trip moves to the
    "heading to pickup" stage and stops when the delivery is completed.
  - Motion data: on supported devices, motion/activity signals are used to
    make location tracking more battery-efficient during a delivery (for
    example, reducing updates when the vehicle is stationary).

  You can disable location access at any time in your device settings.
  Disabling location will limit map, search, and live-tracking features.

2.3 Camera and photo library
  - With your permission, the App uses your camera and photo library to set a
    profile picture, capture proof-of-delivery and transport photos, and
    upload documents. With your permission, the App can also save
    proof-of-delivery photos to your device's photo library.

2.4 Device and technical information
  - Device and app information such as device model, operating system version,
    app version, language/locale, and a push-notification token (see below).
  - Log and diagnostic information generated when you use the Service, used to
    operate, secure, and troubleshoot the App.

2.5 Push notifications
  - We use Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) to deliver push notifications about
    orders, shipments, chat messages, and account activity. To do this, we
    process a device push token associated with your account. You can turn off
    notifications in your device settings.

